      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Produces a string representation of this IntegerLinkedList. The output will start with a left bracket, contain an ordered space-separated sequence of integer values in the list, and end with a right bracket. For example, if called on the empty string, the result would be "[]". If called on the a list whose head node contained 1 and pointed to a final node that contained 3, the output would be "[1 3]" (possibly with additional spaces).
